The paper deals with the problem of nonadaptive noiseless group testing, which involves designing algorithms to detect defective items in a set of N items, where K are defective, using a limited number of tests. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper discusses the performance of several detection algorithms and considers a class of designs for the group testing problem based on Bernoulli random processes. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.LG, and cs.CC, in that order.
